       <blockquote>
        <p><a class="tumblr_blog" href="http://skunkbear.tumblr.com/post/112237281364/nimoy">skunkbear</a>:</p>
        <blockquote>
         <p>Goodbye to my favorite science officer. <br></p>
         <p>Leonard Nimoy, who played Spock on the original <i>Star Trek</i> series, <a href="http://www.npr.org/blogs/thetwo-way/2015/02/27/389516793/leonard-nimoy-mr-spock-on-star-trek-dies-at-83">died today</a>. Nimoy invented the Vulcan salute himself. He was inspired by the Jewish <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Priestly_Blessing">Priestly Blessing</a> he had seen at an Orthodox synagogue.<br></p>
        </blockquote> 
        <p>R.I.P.&nbsp;</p>
       </blockquote> 
       <p>A pic that’s truly worth a thousand words … <br></p> 
