      <div class="post-content"> 
       <p>A view that can boost the body’s immune response? <a class="tumblelog" href="http://tmblr.co/mnQIjaEIkwAf296zT1-hltQ">ucberkeley</a> researchers <a href="http://newscenter.berkeley.edu/2015/02/02/anti-inflammatory/">have found </a>that the awe we feel when we’re in nature (or viewing art or listening to music) may help lower levels of cytokines, which are proteins that signal the immune system to work harder.&nbsp;<br></p> 
